Silicon photonics technology can be used to integrate traditional computing chip technologies with optical networking technologies that use pulses ⁠of light to transmit ‌data.

headline: Nvidia set for $320 billion price swing after earnings, options indicate
summary: NEW YORK (Reuters) -Nvidia's earnings report on Wednesday could trigger a $320 billion swing in the chipmaker's market value — the largest post-earnings move ever ​for the AI giant — as investors seek signals about whether the artificial intelligence boom is accelerating or cooling.  Nvidia ‌options implied about a 7% move for the stock in either direction after it announces its quarterly results, which are expected following the market close on ‌Wednesday, data from analytics firm Option Research & Technology Services (ORATS) showed.  At Nvidia's current market value of about $4.6 trillion, the options-implied move would represent the largest one-day market value change following quarterly earnings for the artificial-intelligence bellwether, a Reuters analysis found.

headline: Gold Wavers on Dimmer Fed Cut Outlook, Jitters Over Tech Stocks
summary: Bullion briefly dipped below $4,000 an ounce, then pared losses, following a three-day drop. While gold often performs well when investors seek haven from market turmoil, it can also suffer in the short-term as traders are forced to unwind leveraged positions.

The bank’s target price for Nvidia is $215, compared to its Monday closing price of $186.60.

headline: Microsoft partners with Anthropic and Nvidia in cloud infrastructure deal
summary: Microsoft said Tuesday it is partnering with artificial intelligence company Anthropic and chipmaker Nvidia as part of a cloud infrastructure deal that moves the software giant further away from its longtime alliance with OpenAI.  Anthropic, maker of the chatbot Claude that competes with OpenAI's ChatGPT, said it is committed to buying $30 billion of computing capacity from Microsoft's Azure cloud computing platform.  As part of the partnership, Nvidia will also invest up to $10 billion in Anthropic, and Microsoft will invest up to $5 billion in the San Francisco-based startup.

headline: Anthropic to Buy $30 Billion of Azure Compute Capacity in Microsoft and Nvidia Partnership
summary: Nvidia  and  Microsoft  have committed to invest up to $10 billion and $5 billion, respectively, in Anthropic as part of a new strategic partnership, the companies announced Tuesday.  Under the terms of the agreement, Anthropic has committed to purchase $30 billion worth of compute capacity and contract up to 1 gigawatt of additional capacity from  Microsoft  as it scales its flagship AI assistant, Claude, on the hyperscaler’s Azure platform.  Nvidia  stock declined 2.5% to $182.01 following the announcement, while Microsoft fell 2.6% to $494.14.

headline: Bitcoin drops below $90,000 for the first time since April then rebounds
summary: Bitcoin briefly fell below $90,000 overnight as investors sell once high-flying assets like cryptocurrencies and artificial intelligence stocks.  Bitcoin fell to around $89,500 early Tuesday, its first drop below $90,000 since April, before recovering to around $93,600 by late morning.  Shares of Robinhood Markets, which have tripled this year on the strength of crypto trading, are down 21% so far in November.

headline: Wall Street drops again as Nvidia, bitcoin and other stars keep swinging
summary: The U.S. stock market is falling again on Tuesday, following a sell-off that swept Asia and Europe, as Nvidia, bitcoin and other Wall Street stars keep swinging on worries that their prices shot too high.  Nvidia was again the heaviest weight on the market, and its drop of 2.9% brought its loss for the month so far to 10.5%.  What Nvidia does matters disproportionately to savers' 401(k) accounts because it's the most influential stock on Wall Street due to its immense size.
